  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for this synthetic accepted-outcome package. The ContextOfUse description enumerates operating ranges (temperature 37 °C ± 1 °C, inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg, outlet pressure 60–120 mmHg, flow rates 3–8 L/min, rotational speeds 2400–3600 RPM, Newtonian blood analogue, fully turbulent regime Re > 4000) in prose, giving the appearance of a defined operating envelope, but no structured hasOperatingEnvelope or hasApplicabilityConstraint link is emitted.",
